emucap — third-party attributions
==================================

emucap integrates with, patches, or loads code into the retro-emulators below.
emucap does NOT redistribute these emulators; each adapter's build.sh downloads
the pinned upstream release and builds it on your machine. The attributions are
provided because emucap's adapter code is a derivative of, or a plugin for, these
projects. Each project remains under its own copyright and license.

Mednafen
  Upstream: https://mednafen.github.io/
  License:  GPL-2.0-or-later (per source-file headers)
  Used by:  adapters/mednafen (emucap.cpp compiled in; also drives Saturn/PSX/PCE/MD)
  Bundles third-party code under GPL-2.0+/LGPL (e.g. hq2x/3x/4x = LGPL).

Flycast
  Upstream: https://github.com/flyinghead/flycast
  License:  GPL-2.0-or-later (Reicast/nullDC lineage)
  Used by:  adapters/flycast (emucap.cpp compiled in; Dreamcast)
  Bundles MIT/BSD/zlib deps (imgui, xxHash, libchdr, ...).

MAME
  Upstream: https://github.com/mamedev/mame
  License:  GPL-2.0-or-later as a whole (majority of files BSD-3-Clause)
  Used by:  adapters/mame-pc98 and adapters/mame-neogeo
            (patches + Lua plugin + GDB bridges; PC-98 and Neo Geo MVS)
  Bundles BSD components (bgfx/bimg/bx, Zstandard, linenoise, ...).

MesenCE
  Upstream: https://github.com/nesdev-org/MesenCE
  Pinned source: 2.2.1 (20ba206cef5ba207c21203176d02cb9f43dda9fb)
  License:  GPL-3.0-or-later
  Used by:  adapters/mesen2 (GPL-3.0-or-later local patch stack and build recipe,
            plus separately loaded GPL-2.0-or-later runtime Lua; SNES/NES/GB/
            GBC/GBA/Game Gear)
  Distribution: emucap does not ship Mesen binaries. Each user builds the pinned
                source plus the complete patch stack on their own machine.

DeSmuME
  Upstream: https://github.com/TASEmulators/desmume
  License:  GPL-2.0-or-later
  Used by:  adapters/desmume-nds (patch stack + GDB bridge; Nintendo DS)

PPSSPP
  Upstream: https://github.com/hrydgard/ppsspp
  License:  GPL-2.0-or-later (per source-file headers)
  Used by:  adapters/ppsspp (patch stack applied to the source tree, compiled into
            PPSSPPHeadless; PSP)
  Bundles third-party code under its own license in ext/, notably FFmpeg, plus zlib,
  zstd, snappy, lzma-sdk, libpng, libzip, libchdr, freetype, glew, glslang, SPIRV-Cross,
  vulkan/vma, basis_universal, xbrz, jpge, stb, nanosvg, minimp3/at3_standalone, libkirk,
  armips, udis86, cityhash, sha1, sfmt, cpu_features, rapidjson, pugixml, gason, sol/lua,
  imgui, portable-file-dialogs, discord-rpc, miniupnp, rcheevos, OpenXR-SDK, libadrenotools.

PCSX2
  Upstream: https://github.com/PCSX2/pcsx2
  Pinned source: v2.6.3 (bc8151d2a46d4aba039ea5580afbfc7bfcf6d730)
  License:  GPL-3.0-or-later (per source-file SPDX headers)
  Used by:  adapters/pcsx2 (GPL-3.0-or-later patch stack; PlayStation 2)
  The separate Rust PINE bridge is GPL-2.0-or-later project code.
  Distribution: emucap ships source patches and a build recipe, not PCSX2
                binaries, BIOS files, or game media.

Dolphin
  Upstream: https://github.com/dolphin-emu/dolphin
  License:  GPL-2.0-or-later
  Used by:  adapters/dolphin (native patch stack; GameCube and Wii)
  Distribution: emucap ships source patches and a build recipe, not Dolphin
                binaries, keys, firmware, or game media.

Mupen64Plus
  Upstream: https://github.com/mupen64plus
  Pinned source: 2.6.0 (core b0d68c20f49b8f833afa21450e0e8874c87c13c4)
  License: GNU GPL version 2 for the core and selected plugins; representative
           source-file headers permit version 2 or later. Bundled components
           retain their LGPL, BSD, zlib/libpng, and Bitstream notices.
  Used by: adapters/mupen64plus (source-build recipe and dynamically loaded
           debugger core/plugins; Nintendo 64)
  Distribution: emucap ships the frontend source and build recipe, not emulator
                binaries or game media. The upstream GPL test ROM remains in the
                ignored local build tree.

Upstream license determinations were made from each project's source-file SPDX
headers and README, not from the bare COPYING boilerplate.
